comments.body:
@jhoneill That's quite an investigation and write-up! I propose two extra solutions which may be simpler:
1. At the end of `Set-Location`, if the path can be simplified, set location to the simplified one
2. Since this is mostly a visual bug, simplify location if possible only in the prompt

I vote for option 2, as it is less likely to be a breaking change if some edge case relies on the current location being in this weird long form.

@ThomasLey You can test if `function Prompt { (Resolve-Path Get-Location) -replace $HOME, '~' }` solves your issue, if not then try replacing `Resolve-Path` with some other function.
